The measurement of the electron energy probability function (EEPF) has been firstly performed in 2007 by combination of the rf-compensated Langmuir probe and an analog differentiation technique (Takahashi et al. 2007), showing the depleted tail of the EEPF rather than the ‘beam’ electrons (Fig. 9a), which is very similar to the 1D-PIC result. Furthermore, the slope of the EEPF measured downstream of the CFDL (Fig. 9b) coincides that of the tail in the upstream EEPF. The break energy εbreak\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
