				\begin{document}$$T_{\text {B}}$$\end{document} term. This fact implies that the electron pressure in the magnetic nozzle is mainly balanced with the magnetic pressure force, rather than the electrostatic force, indicating the validity of the simplified electron-diamagnetic thruster models (Fruchtman 2006; Takahashi et al. 2011b; Fruchtman et al. 2012).

