				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} v^2 \simeq v_{\text {A}}^2 = \frac{B^2}{\mu \rho } = \frac{(B_v+\varDelta B)^2}{\mu \rho }. \end{aligned}$$\end{document}This implies that the velocity v cannot exceed the Alfvén velocity calculated from the total magnetic field. In other words, the plasma flow can increase the magnetic field (ΔBz>0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
